The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, held a briefing on December 22, 2009. The briefing covered various topics including health care reform, Iran, OPEC, the President's involvement in the legislative process, the economy, and upcoming plans for the President's vacation. Gibbs also addressed questions about the death of Ann Nixon Cooper and the use of language by politicians. He declined to comment on specific legal cases or pardons and stated that he was not aware of the details regarding a recent ruling by a commander in northern Iraq.